<plot>In the style of a Chris Marker essay film, Hotel Saudade follows Cameron Bailey on a journey to Brazil. Prompted by a failed love and a disturbing pursuit of danger, this film critic picks up a camera and goes looking for a picture -- a picture of the woman he loved, a picture of an accident, a self-portrait.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?247119</url></doc>
